# Change log ↔ App summary (always)

After **meaningful** work in **`GoDiveMVP/`** (features, UX, data rules, navigation, models, tests that reflect new behavior), update **both** docs in the **same effort**:

1. **`GoDiveMVP/cursor/change_log.md`** — append to the **latest open section** (the highest-numbered section that is **not** marked **`(pushed)`**). Add a short **Summary** line plus bullets for files / tests as needed.
2. **`GoDiveMVP/cursor/app_summary.md`** — refresh the relevant high-level sections so architecture and user-visible behavior match the code **now**.

## Section rules

- Append work to the **latest open** section (highest number, **not** marked **`(pushed)`**).
- After a **successful `git push`** in the same task (following a commit that included the work), mark that section **`(pushed)`** and add the **next** empty numbered header per **`.cursor/rules/changelog-mark-pushed-on-git-push.mdc`**. The user may also ask to mark pushed / open the next section without you pushing.
- **Do not** mark **`(pushed)`** if the push failed or only local commits exist without a requested push.
- When the user asks for a **new** section outside a push (e.g. “start §47”): ensure the prior section is **`(pushed)`**, add **`## NN - …`** (title only; no **`(not pushed)`** line unless the user wants it), and sync **`app_summary.md`** for everything in the closed section.

## `app_summary.md` scope

Update as relevant (synthesize; do not paste the whole changelog):

- App shell, tabs, navigation, headers / page wrappers
- SwiftData models and data flow (import, seed, delete)
- Notable screens and user-visible flows
- Testing / seeding strategy

Keep **`app_summary.md`** readable and current — not a duplicate of every changelog bullet.

## Incomplete handoff

Do **not** treat doc updates as optional: if code shipped in the latest section’s scope, **`change_log.md`** and **`app_summary.md`** must reflect it before you consider the task done.
